*** BEGIN IMPORTANT NOTE ***

The callback functions in these samples should be studied closely
to get a sense of how libcurl.vb is implemented. You will see that
this is a pretty low-level API.

*** END IMPORTANT NOTE ***

These are trivial examples to demonstrate the basic functionality
of libcurl.vb.

The samples include:

-- Buffer.cls: Trivial VB class used to demonstrate the passing of
               a class object (IUnknown interface) to a callback
               via the extra parameter.

-- EasyGet.bas: Retrieve a web page.

-- FTPUpload.bas: Upload a file to an FTP site.

-- Headers.bas: Dump headers, demonstrating HEADERFUNCTION bas.

-- InfoDemo.bas: Dump CURLINFO data received after a download.

-- MultiDemo.bas: Retrieve two URLs using the Multi interface.

-- MultiPartForm.bas: Demonstrate RFC 1867 multi-part upload.

-- SSLGet.bas: Retrive an https web page.

-- VersionData.bas: Dump internal cURL version data.\

-- Project1.vbp: sample gui and test code for single 
                 thread download to mem or file -dz

